            "label": "Describe the purpose and impact of the programmatic or language request (Max 500 words)",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": false,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Restores funding to $9 billion to sustain U.S. leadership in space science and maintain a competitive edge over international rivals like China.\n* Ensures workforce stability for the aerospace industrial base, preventing the loss of specialized skills following recent budget volatility.\n* Implements the scientific community's consensus priorities for the next decade of discovery as codified in the National Academies Decadal Surveys.\n* Provides high returns on investment in discovery, national prestige, and practical applications ranging from planetary defense to climate monitoring.",
            "rationale": "Summarizes core advocacy talking points regarding U.S. leadership, competition, workforce, and scientific roadmaps.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_1234966063:3c955b14e646",
            "label": "How will this programmatic or language request help your organization, CA-35, California, and/or the nation? Please prioritize district impact. (Max 150 words)",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Directly supports $1.55 million in recent NASA Science obligations within CA-35 institutions and businesses.\n* Sustains a $1.66M active award for Mindrum Precision Inc. in Rancho Cucamonga to manufacture microvalves for the Dragonfly mission to Titan.\n* Funds critical research at Cal Poly Pomona and Ocean Motion Technologies in Pomona, advancing mission assurance and Earth observation capabilities.\n* Strengthens the local STEM pipeline and supports high-skill employment in the district's aerospace and technology sectors.",
            "rationale": "Cites specific CA-35 spending data, including recipients Mindrum Precision, Cal Poly Pomona, and Ocean Motion Technologies.",
            "confidence": "high"
