        "recipient_id": "00e87d8a-68ce-1c11-017b-a60de06a9263-C",
        "award_amount": 249105.0,
        "description": "The proposed project aims to enhance the management and Conservation of the Ross Sea Region Marine Protected Area (RSRMPA) through the implementation of the big blue cloud  a cloud-based data science open platform developed by Ocean Motion Technologies (OMT). By integrating NASA Earth observations with in-situ datasets  the project will provide critical support for evidence-based decision-making  significantly improving the effectiveness of Conservation efforts in the rsrmpa. Established in 2016 by the Commission for the Conservation of Antarctic Marine Living Resources (CCAMLR)  the rsrmpa aims to protect ecologically significant areas from the primary threats of fishing and climate change. However  its success depends on robust management  involving active research and continuous monitoring to assess changes in ecosystem structure and function. Our data platform will address critical gaps in current Conservation efforts. These include sparse and infrequent observations  single-discipline research  and fragmented stakeholder engagement. The platform offers a comprehensive data science environment for hosting  synthesizing  analyzing  and visualizing diverse datasets. Key functionalities include robust data governance  version control  advanced analytics  and interactive dashboards.",
